reviewText: Some of the movies are dark, but i love Judi Dench enough to watch her no matter what.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: This was a good movie too. Anyone who likes Judi Dench will like it.She is such a versatile actress and one of the best.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: This collection surprised me with the age of some of the dramas.  It was not what I expected but it shows where Ms Dench came from and is a study of her career performances.  Much of it is old but like good wine just matures with age.Worth watching if your a serious follower of theatre.  Not light weight fluffy nothings.  Good and Ill watch it again and again Im sure.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: This collection would likely appeal most to loyal Judi Dench fans. Some selections appeal more than others, but all are interesting, especially as one studies the acting expertise and style of the principals.
summary: A Must for Judi Dench Fans
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: Dame Judi is a remarkable woman, and these DVDs are a remarkable collection of the work that made her famous!  Long live Dame Judi!!!!
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: The hearing impaired reading that the set is advertized as "Closed Captioned" need to be warned that the captions are defective and mostly unreadable.  Every so often they read fine, than gibberish.  Too bad, the set otherwisd looks fine.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: EXCELLENT SET. ALL THE BEST ADJECTIVES MUST BE ADDRESSED TO ANYTHING PROPOSED HERE, BUT AS A STRANGER I HAVE BOUGHT THE SET BECAUSE WE ARE INFORMED IT IS 'CLOSED CAPTIONED' AND I AM TOLD IT MEANS IT HAS SUBTITLES.THE SET I RECEIVED HAS NO SUBTITLES. NOT AT ALL. I AM TOLD THE SAME SET RELEASED IN U.K. HAS INDEED SUBTITLES. I HAVE WRITTEN TO BBC AMERICA BUT I GOT NO ANSWER WHICH IS TOO BAD ... ISN'T IT?ERNESTO OPPICELLI - GENOVA CERTOSA - ITALY
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: Proof that Ms. Dench is one of our finest actresses today.  An important set to own and cherish!  And as "icing to the cake" her superb rendition of "Send in the Clowns" is included.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)

reviewText: Absolutely great!  Judi Dench is the best of the best, and it's a real privilege to at last be able to see some of her extraordinary early work, along with some of her more recent, highly acclaimed roles as well.  The special features are treasures.
Title: The Judi Dench Collection: (The Cherry Orchard / Talking to a Stranger / Keep an Eye on Amélie / Going Gently / Ghosts / and more)
